  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Trim the green stalk off your <strong>aubergine[s]</strong> and cut into quarters, lengthways, then chop into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the<strong> chopped aubergine</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a generous drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 20 min or until golden and tender</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1592234002649-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1592234002649-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1592234002649-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1592234002649-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1592234002649-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the aubergine is roasting, chop your<strong> cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Add your<strong> fennel seeds</strong> to a<strong> pestle & mortar</strong> and grind to a fine powder</p><p>Tip: Don't have a pestle and mortar? Chop them up as finely as you can</p><p>Boil a kettle</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1592234025760-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1592234025760-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1592234025760-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1592234025760-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1592234025760-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add<strong> half</strong> your <strong>'Nduja</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the pan and cook for 1-2 min or until it begins to release some oil</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong> and <strong>crushed fennel seeds </strong>(not a fan of aniseed? Only add a little!) to the pan and cook for 2-3 min or until the tomatoes are beginning to soften</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1592234183836-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1592234183836-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1592234183836-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
